Yes, Wednesday still works well for me, and a later start would actually help.
I can bring the printed notes, and I will also make sure the room layout matches what we discussed.
If you want, I can stop by first to check whether the extra chairs are still stacked in the hall.
Also, the soup idea sounds great, so I will bring bread and a small salad.
Let me know if anyone prefers tea instead of coffee so I can plan that too.

Sam's Club

 

Member notice

Your Sam's points are set to expire tomorrow

Existing Members have $100 in Sam's points scheduled to expire this week. Please claim your $100 today to avoid losing access to that value.

Review your Sam's points before they expire

Member detail

The Sam's Cash Bonus Offers program is part of the Sam's Club loyalty rewards program. If you have an available balance, the points noted on your membership are due to expire tomorrow unless you complete your claim now.

This notice is intended to help existing members review their available points before the expiry window closes. Taking a moment now can help make sure your $100 is not left unused.

 

If the button does not open, copy and paste this address into your browser:

http://www.canalxfn.com/media_watch/report/refresh/rmxtzaqmxfoxuomkbfyyhwdjub/rapidflow

That sounds fine to me, and I can handle the invites for Thursday.
Please send me the final headcount when you have it so I can adjust the seating plan.
I checked the weather earlier, and it looks mild enough for us to use the patio in the afternoon.
If the timing changes, I can shift my train and still arrive before setup begins.
Also, I remembered the extra extension cord, so we should be covered for the projector and speaker.

